The paper discusses the use of model-driven engineering and domain-specific transformation languages in the context of component and connector architecture description languages. This topic falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of grammars to derive domain-specific transformation languages, which falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for model transformation, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the need for maintaining and evolving models, which falls under the software development (cs.SD) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of domain-specific languages, which falls under the data structures and algorithms (cs.DL) sub-category.
